<task id="080" project="sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair">
  <metadata>
    <title>P4.A1 — Update `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` with "Test update obligation" section (FR-22)</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>45-60 minutes</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent (main session only)</assigned>
    <tags>phase-4, governance, anti-drift, constraint, main-session-only</tags>
    <parallel-group>4-main-seq</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Main-session-only — sub-agent write boundary per root CLAUDE.md §3 prohibits sub-agent edits to `.claude/` paths. Task-execute MUST refuse Agent delegation; main session edits this file directly.</parallel-reason>
    <main-session-only>true</main-session-only>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Update `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` (the binding pre-merge checklist for every BFF-touching task per root CLAUDE.md §10) to add a NEW section titled "Test update obligation". This section is the durable anti-drift mechanism: it codifies that any PR modifying `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/` MUST include corresponding test additions/updates. Exceptions require explicit code review sign-off citing reason.

    Per design.md §5.5, this is one of three coordinated anti-drift mechanisms (this constraint + PR template question via task 081 + code review checklist line via task 082). Tasks 081, 082, 083 cross-reference this section. Without this constraint codified, the other governance updates have nothing to reference.

    🚨 CRITICAL — task-execute MUST refuse Agent delegation for this task. Main session edits this file directly via the Edit tool. Per root CLAUDE.md §3, sub-agents launched via Agent tool CANNOT write to `.claude/` paths; attempting delegation will fail with "Edit denied on `.claude/...`". This is the boundary working correctly. The main session is the ONLY agent permitted to perform this edit.

    NO production code changes. NO test changes. Constraint document update only.
  </prompt>

  <role>Main-session AI agent codifying anti-drift governance into the binding BFF-extensions constraint document.</role>

  <goal>
    `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` updated with a NEW section "Test update obligation" containing:
    - The binding rule statement (PRs modifying `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/` MUST include corresponding test additions/updates)
    - The exception clause (requires explicit code review sign-off citing reason)
    - Forward-reference to PR template (FR-23 task 081) and code review checklist (FR-24 task 082)
    - Forward-reference to root CLAUDE.md §10 (FR-25 task 083 will add the reverse cross-reference)

    Existing sections in the constraint file are PRESERVED unchanged (additive edit only). The constraint remains a pre-merge checklist; the new section integrates into that structure.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="target-file">.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="FR-22">`.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` gains a "Test update obligation" section detailing the binding rule + exception clause; cross-referenced from CLAUDE.md §10 (verified by task 083)</constraint>
    <constraint source="design.md §5.5">Anti-drift enforcement via code review checklist + PR template question (NOT a CI script); this constraint is the canonical reference cited by both</constraint>
    <constraint source="root CLAUDE.md §3">Sub-agent write boundary: sub-agents CANNOT write to `.claude/` paths. Main session ONLY for this edit.</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">No production code changes (`.claude/constraints/` is project doc, not `src/`)</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-09">Task POML metadata declares `repair-not-rewrite: true`</constraint>
    <constraint source="root CLAUDE.md §10">BFF Hygiene binds: any task adding to BFF surface area MUST load `bff-extensions.md`. This update extends the obligation to test-coverage</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
