  <context>
    <background>
      Per design.md §5.5 (anti-drift enforcement, locked decision 2026-05-30), this project chose Option D (code review checklist + PR template question) over Option C (CI script). The CI script was rejected because: (a) doc-only PRs would false-positive; (b) refactor PRs with unchanged-but-still-valid tests would false-positive; (c) owner direction was "do not over-burden PR process." The constraint file `bff-extensions.md` is the canonical reference cited by both the PR template (task 081) and the code review checklist (task 082). Without the constraint section codified here, the other tasks have nothing to cross-reference. This task is the first link in the anti-drift chain.

      Per root CLAUDE.md §3, sub-agents launched via Agent tool CANNOT write to `.claude/` paths. Task-execute MUST refuse Agent delegation for this task — main session edits the file directly. Tasks 081 (`.github/`), 082 (`docs/`), 084, 085, 086 are agent-safe; tasks 080 and 083 are main-session-only.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="P2+P3" status="substantially-complete">Project is at zero-failure target close (or close to it) — governance update lands when repair body of work is in final shape</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` in full to understand existing structure (section order, formatting conventions, cross-reference style).</step>
    <step order="2">Identify the most appropriate insertion point for the new "Test update obligation" section. Likely candidate: just after the existing pre-merge checklist section, or as a NEW top-level section near the file's coverage governance discussion. Preserve all existing sections unchanged.</step>
    <step order="3">Draft the new section "Test update obligation". Contents:
      (a) Binding rule: "When a PR modifies `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/`, it MUST include corresponding test additions or updates in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/` (matching the modified service's path)."
      (b) Exception clause: "Exceptions require explicit code review sign-off citing reason (e.g., 'test already covers new behavior via existing parametric case', 'change is internal refactor with no behavioral surface area')."
      (c) Enforcement: "Enforced by (1) PR template question (`.github/pull_request_template.md`); (2) code review checklist (`docs/procedures/testing-and-code-quality.md`); (3) reviewer judgment per this constraint. NOT enforced by CI script (design.md §5.5 — over-engineering against the wrong failure mode)."
      (d) Cross-reference: "See root `CLAUDE.md` §10 for BFF Hygiene binding context."
    </step>
    <step order="4">Apply the edit via the Edit tool (main session only — DO NOT delegate to sub-agent). Verify the section is inserted; existing sections are unchanged.</step>
    <step order="5">Read the modified file and confirm: (a) new section present and complete; (b) existing pre-merge checklist still intact; (c) cross-reference to root CLAUDE.md §10 included.</step>
    <step order="6">Verify `git status` shows ONLY `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` modified (no `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`, or any other path).</step>
    <step order="7">Commit message: "docs(.claude): add 'Test update obligation' section to bff-extensions.md (FR-22)" — references FR-22 from spec.md.</step>
    <step order="8">Update `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/current-task.md` with completion + cite the new section heading + paragraph count.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">`.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` for current structure</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Append new "Test update obligation" section; preserve existing sections</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">`git status` for boundary verification</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs">.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md (updated with new "Test update obligation" section)</output>
  </outputs>

